All committers have signed the CLA.
@mannol what's your input on this? I'm totally unfamiliar with vp8, I assume that you are more familiar than most of us here.
@zoff99 Are you sure that increase `kf_max_dist` will not lead to problems on low bandwidth? More oftec keyframes requeres more bundwith

Haven't tried myself but i think this will help with video quality. Regarding bandwidth: it should be controlled by the bitrate primarily. Even though this will probably increase bandwidth usage, it's still not as important factor for it as the bitrate (didn't measure myself but I'm sure that's the case).

@Diadlo actually in my tests it requires less bandwidth. why? with these simple tweaks i can now set a lower video bitrate and it will work ok. before with low bitrate setting the video corrputed always and never recovered.
tests are difficult because there is only 1 client for low bandwidth (android 3G connection) now (it's not Antox). so the results are statistically not really valid.

@mannol there is no documentation what clients should set as video bitrate. i made some experiments and this is my result.
i also tried some other settings:

* cfg.g_error_resilient -> still does not work even with VP9
* cfg.g_lag_in_frames -> results in no video
* cfg.g_threads -> any value results in no video
* cfg.rc_dropframe_thresh = 25 -> works, but i see no difference

what i have **not** yet tried:

* vpx_codec_control(&new_c, VP8E_SET_CPUUSED, 16);  -> here VP8 can take up to "16" maybe that will help? make it user configurable? now we use "8"

```
VP8E_SET_CPUUSED 
Codec control function to set encoder internal speed settings. 
Changes in this value influences, among others, the encoder's
selection of motion estimation methods. Values greater than 0 will
increase encoder speed at the expense of quality.

Note:
Valid range for VP8: -16..16
Valid range for VP9: -8..8

```
